item.title: Colombia’s air force kills 20 ELN rebels
item.description: Colombia's air force has bombed a camp of the National Liberation Army (ELN), a guerrilla group, killing one of its most wanted leaders, Defence Minister Carlos Holmes Trujillo announced.

item.title: No Macquarie interest in BT’s Openreach
item.description: BT Group is in talks to sell a multi-billion pound stake in its wholly-owned network subsidiary Openreach to infrastructure investors to help fund an ambitious expansion in fibre broadband, the Financial Times reports.

item.title: UK holds 8th week of applause for carers
item.description: Britons have joined in a weekly round of applause to pay tribute to care workers and hospital staff as the country gingerly starts to return to work.

item.title: US lacks vaccine plan, whistleblower says
item.description: Whistleblower Rick Bright says the US lacks a plan to produce and fairly distribute a coronavirus vaccine when it becomes available.

item.title: France’s virus death toll edges over Spain
item.description: France's cumulative coronavirus death has toll edged back above Spain's as the health ministry reported that the number of people who died of COVID-19 in the past 24 hours increased by 351 or 1.3 per cent to 27,425.

item.title: US senator steps aside, FBI probes trades
item.description: US Senator Richard Burr says he is stepping aside as chairman of the Senate Intelligence Committee after the FBI seized his mobile phone during an investigation of stock trades he made before the sharp market downturn triggered by the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: Governments offer more economic relief
item.description: European governments have promised more relief to their citizens as a top US immunologist said the country faces its "darkest winter in modern history" unless leaders act decisively to prevent a rebound of the coronavirus.

item.title: Trump ‘disappointed’ with China over virus
item.description: US President Donald Trump is "very disappointed" in China over its failure to contain the novel coronavirus, saying the worldwide pandemic cast a pall over his US-China trade deal.

item.title: Russian science minister catches virus
item.description: Russian science minister Valery Falkov has recovered after contracting the coronavirus, Russian President Vladimir Putin says.

item.title: Italy daily virus death toll, new cases up
item.description: Deaths from the COVID-19 epidemic in Italy have climbed by 262 against 195 the day before, the Civil Protection Agency says, while the daily tally of new cases rose to 992 from 888 on the prior day.
